data.chText: （因理解或判断失误）搞错的
data.enText: wrong because you have understood or judged a situation badly

data.chText: 她是要帮忙，只是想法不对头。
data.enText: She only did it in a misguided attempt to help.

data.text: wrong ♦ false ♦ mistaken ♦ incorrect ♦ inaccurate ♦ misguided ♦ untrue

data.chText: 以上各词均指错误、不正确、犯错。
data.enText: These words all describe sth that is not right or correct, or sb who is not right about sth.
wrong

data.chText: 指错误的、不正确的，（人）出错、搞错、有错误：
data.enText: not right or correct; (of a person) not right about sb/sth

data.chText: 我的答案全都错了。
data.enText: I got all the answers wrong.

data.chText: 我们错误地以为她会同意。
data.enText: We were wrong to assume she'd agree.
false

data.chText: 指不正确的、不真实的、错误的 ：
data.enText: not true or correct; wrong because it is based on sth that is not true or correct

data.chText: 鲸鱼是鱼，对还是错？
data.enText: A whale is a fish. True or false?

data.chText: 她向保险公司提供了不真实的资料。
data.enText: She gave false information to the insurance company.
mistaken

data.chText: 指意见或判断不正确的、以错误的意见或判断为基础的：
data.enText: wrong in your opinion or judgement; based on a wrong opinion or bad judgement

data.chText: 你对简的看法完全错了。
data.enText: You're completely mistaken about Jane.
incorrect

data.chText: 指与事实不符的、不准确的、不正确的：
data.enText: ( rather formal ) wrong according to the facts; containing mistakes

data.chText: 这些数字有许多是不准确的。
data.enText: Many of the figures were incorrect.
inaccurate

data.chText: 指与事实不符的、不准确的、不正确的：
data.enText: wrong according to the facts; containing mistakes

data.chText: 这报告没有经过认真调查，相当不实。
data.enText: The report was badly researched and quite inaccurate.

data.chText: 用incorrect还是inaccurate？
事实、数据或拼写错误用incorrect；以错误事实为基础的信息、看法或描述可用incorrect或inaccurate；影片、报告或地图等制品与事实不符用inaccurate。
data.enText: A fact, figure or spelling that is wrong is incorrect ; information, a belief or a description based on incorrect facts can be incorrect or inaccurate ; something that is produced, such as a film, report or map, that contains incorrect facts is inaccurate .
incorrect or inaccurate?
misguided

data.chText: 指理解、判断失误的：
data.enText: wrong because you have understood or judged a situation badly

data.chText: 她想帮忙，但做法不对头，反而把事情弄得更糟。
data.enText: In her misguided attempts to help, she only made the situation worse.
untrue

data.chText: 指无事实根据的、捏造的、猜想的：
data.enText: not based on facts, but invented or guessed

data.chText: 这些指控纯属捏造。
data.enText: These accusations are totally untrue.
be wrong/mistaken about sth
to prove wrong/false/mistaken/incorrect/inaccurate/misguided/untrue
wrong/false/mistaken/incorrect/inaccurate/untrue information
a(n) false/mistaken/incorrect/inaccurate/misguided belief
a(n) wrong/incorrect answer
absolutely/completely/totally/quite wrong/false/mistaken/incorrect/inaccurate/misguided/untrue
It is/would be wrong/false/incorrect/inaccurate/untrue to say…

tr: wrong in e.g. opinion or judgment

example: an ill-conceived plan to take over the company

value.def: If you describe an opinion or plan as misguided, you are critical of it because you think it is based on an incorrect idea. You can also describe people as misguided.

example.ex: In a misguided attempt to be funny, he manages only offensiveness...
example.tran: 他本想表现得风趣一点，却弄巧成拙地冒犯了别人。

example.ex: He is misguided in expecting honesty from her.
example.tran: 他误以为她能够以诚相待。

value.tran: (观点、计划)受错误思想引导的；（人）被错误地引导的，被引入歧途的
